NAME: DISTCORR

distcorr routine in distcorr.pro

NAME: DISTCORR PURPOSE: Apply DISTANCE correction based upon provided factors : There is a big assumption here, that is that the DISTFACTOR = R/R0 ; where R0=1AU The correction based up a 1/R^2 assumption, or Corrected Flux = Input Flux * 1.0/(DISTFACTOR)^2 OPTIONAL INPUT PARAMETERS VERBOSE : Set if reporting of details is desired (default=0) TIME_IN_S: Set if the time is in seconds instead of ms DEBUG : Set to report additional information useful in debugging.
